  "informal_statement": "For every pair of natural numbers m, n: m! * n! <= (m+n)! (equivalently, the binomial coefficient C(m+n,n) = (m+n)!/(m!n!) is a positive integer).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Two-parameter induction: fix m and induct on n. Base case n=0: m!*0! = m!*1 = m! = (m+0)!. Successor case: rewrite (m+n+1)! and (n+1)! via Nat.factorial_succ to get the goal m!*((n+1)*n!) <= (m+n+1)*(m+n)!; multiply the inductive hypothesis m!*n! <= (m+n)! by (n+1) (Nat.mul_le_mul_left), then nlinarith closes the remainder using that (n+1) <= (m+n+1) and (m+n)! > 0.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem factorial_add_ge_mul (m n : ℕ) : m.factorial * n.factorial ≤ (m + n).factorial",
